1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,051
Chapter 7 Manage Your Environment Go First Class Your mind is an amazing mechanism.

2
00:00:10,161 --> 00:00:15,490
When your mind works one way, it can carry you forward to outstanding success.

3
00:00:15,680 --> 00:00:20,770
But the same mind operating in a different manner can produce a total failure.

4
00:00:21,441 --> 00:00:26,371
The mind is the most delicate, most sensitive instrument in all creation.

5
00:00:26,560 --> 00:00:30,851
Let's look now and see what makes the mind think the way it does.

6
00:00:31,201 --> 00:00:33,810
Millions of people are diet-conscious.

7
00:00:33,841 --> 00:00:36,051
We're a calorie-counting nation.

8
00:00:36,241 --> 00:00:41,651
We spend millions of dollars on vitamins, minerals, and other dietary supplements.

9
00:00:41,841 --> 00:00:43,331
And we all know why.

10
00:00:43,521 --> 00:00:49,571
Through nutritional research, we've learned that the body reflects the diet fed the body.

11
00:00:49,761 --> 00:00:58,051
Physical stamina, resistance to disease, body size, even how long we live are all closely related to what we eat.

12
00:00:58,561 --> 00:01:01,331
The body is what the body is fed.

13
00:01:01,601 --> 00:01:05,890
By the same token, the mind is what the mind is fed.

14
00:01:06,401 --> 00:01:11,250
Mind food, of course, doesn't come in packages, and you can't buy it at the store.

15
00:01:11,441 --> 00:01:18,851
Mind food is your environment, all the countless things that influence your conscious and subconscious thought.

16
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:24,931
The kind of mind food we consume determines our habits, attitudes, personality.

17
00:01:25,280 --> 00:01:29,011
Each of us inherited a certain capacity to develop.

18
00:01:29,280 --> 00:01:34,691
But how much of that capacity we have developed, and the way we have developed that capacity,

19
00:01:34,881 --> 00:01:38,051
depends on the kind of mind food we feed it.

20
00:01:38,481 --> 00:01:45,491
The mind reflects what its environment feeds it, just as surely as the body reflects the food you feed it.

21
00:01:46,161 --> 00:01:53,411
Have you ever thought what kind of person you would be had you been reared in some foreign country instead of the United States?

22
00:01:53,601 --> 00:01:55,970
What kinds of foods would you prefer?

23
00:01:56,081 --> 00:01:58,931
Would your preferences for clothing be the same?

24
00:01:59,041 --> 00:02:01,810
What sort of entertainment would you like the most?

25
00:02:02,001 --> 00:02:04,131
What kind of work would you be doing?

26
00:02:04,241 --> 00:02:06,131
What would your religion be?

27
00:02:06,641 --> 00:02:10,530
You can't, of course, be sure of the answers to these questions,

28
00:02:10,640 --> 00:02:16,690
but chances are you would be a materially different person had you grown up in a different country.

29
00:02:16,880 --> 00:02:17,491
Why?

30
00:02:17,841 --> 00:02:21,491
Because you would have been influenced by a different environment.

31
00:02:21,681 --> 00:02:25,651
As the saying goes, you are a product of your environment.

32
00:02:26,241 --> 00:02:27,331
Mark it well.

33
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:31,410
Environment shapes us, makes us think the way we do.

34
00:02:31,841 --> 00:02:38,211
Try to name just one habit or one mannerism you have that you did not pick up from other people.

35
00:02:38,560 --> 00:02:45,491
Relatively minor things, like the way we walk, cough, hold a cup, our preferences for music,

36
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:51,410
literature, entertainment, clothing, all stem in very large part from environment.

37
00:02:52,000 --> 00:03:00,690
More important, the size of your thinking, your goals, your attitudes, your very personality is formed by your environment.

38
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:06,051
Prolonged association with negative people makes us think negatively.

39
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:10,931
Close contact with petty individuals develops petty habits in us.
